                        This journey led me to share what I'd learned. As an instructor, I've guided <strong>more than 250 sincere seekers</strong> from across the world—students who came with open hearts and left with music flowing through their fingertips.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Teaching revealed a beautiful truth: <strong>every student is the flute's next chosen one</strong>, and my role is simply to create the space where that choice can unfold.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="about-section about-section-4">
                    <p>
                        Today, I am fully devoted to this ancient instrument and to the seekers who find their way to it. The bansuri is <strong>not a hobby or a skill</strong>—it is a meditation, a conversation with something timeless.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Together, we explore its depth with patience, clarity, and the kind of ease that only comes when you stop struggling and start <strong>listening</strong>.
                    </p>
                </div>
